column5: I was wondering if anyone knows where I can source walleye jigs like in the attached pic. Note the Green and Black jigs. They seem to have a black/dark silver hook on them that is strong, sharp and doesn't rust anywhere near some of the other ones out there. If anyone knows where I can source these in multiple colours and sizes let me know.  Thanks.
Angling specialties on hwy 7 and keele Pro j on sheppard and warden

Go see Laurie at The Dixie tackle shop in st thomas she has some really nice darter heads (unpainted) with gammy hooks that would be great for eye's but she will order anything for you she's great to deal with
That yellow one is in rough shape. Caught up in the rocks?
Ive switched over to Lindy Exchange jigs almost exclusively. Very high quality hooks (points dont deform in the rocks) and you can swap weights/colours whenever you need
http://lurepartsonline.com/cart.php?m=product_list&c=1968  I have used these in the past, they have a good strong hook in them. Limited color selection though. Black works with everything?
Lol yes it's just there as an example it has the cheaper hook on it
They look like Mustad hooks that are available at www.luremaking.com  if you knew someone with jig molds. I'd help you out but I don't have the hooks at the moment.

I use owner flipping jig hooks on my walleye jigs for weed fishing, the eye comes out on a 30 degree angle, and I custom made my mold to take those hooks, they are tough, and extremely sharpe, and they pull through weeds like a knife through butter, I also use the same hooks for my tube jigs as well, they are expensive, and if im fishin rocks etc I will use mustad ultra-points instead
